OL,6,F'Matthew Bryant was a much-loved
OL,7,Fhusband and popular landlord, and his
OL,8,Fmurder was carried out in cold blood
OL,9,Fby a calculating offender.
OL,11,F'Langley set about carrying out a
OL,12,Fviolent and unprovoked attack on her
OL,13,Fvictim, in broad daylight in front of
OL,14,Fhorrified customers, with little
OL,15,Fregard to the consequences.
OL,17,F'As the investigating officer, I would
OL,18,Flike to place on record my thanks to
OL,19,Fthose who witnessed this tragic
OL,20,Fincident and had the courage to help
OL,21,Fus as we carried out enquiries.'
